t-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;be1f5612-8971-49a2-b640-87a62aca7441&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Five years ago I was sitting around drinking a beer with my college buddy Dayv. I was scrolling through Twitter and watching people get mad at Donald Trump&#8217;s latest outrage, and I said &#8220;You know&#8230;fifteen years ago, the internet was an escape from the real world. Now the real world is an escape from the internet.&#8221; &#8220;Tweet that!&#8221;, Dayv said, so I did. That &#8230;&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;The internet wants to be fragmented&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2022-12-16T22:40:40.019Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6ec79951-fd6d-4552-8163-d2c069e3000b_1440x799.png&quot;,&quot;cover_image_alt&quot;:null,&quot;canonical_url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-internet-wants-to-be-fragmented&quot;,&quot;section_name&quot;:null,&quot;id&quot;:91066659,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;reaction_count&quot;:544,&quot;comment_count&quot;:130,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Noahpinion&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04281755-2cd6-42e5-a496-e69153abebb2_281x281.png&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false}"></div><p>您可以在使用统计数据中看到这种演变。 Twitter 和 Instagram 的使用率呈下降趋势： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F072101a3-fa2a-4d35-9a92-273c606e587a_748x626.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F072101a3-fa2a-4d35-9a92-273c606e587a_748x626.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F072101a3-fa2a-4d35-9a92-273c606e587a_748x626.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F072101a3-fa2a-4d35-9a92-273c606e587a_748x626.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F072101a3-fa2a-4d35-9a92-273c606e587a_748x626.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F072101a3-fa2a-4d35-9a92-273c606e587a_748x626.jpeg" width="668" height="559.048128342246" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/072101a3-fa2a-4d35-9a92-273c606e587a_748x626.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:626,&quot;width&quot;:748,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:668,&quot;bytes&quot;:78640,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F072101a3-fa2a-4d35-9a92-273c606e587a_748x626.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F072101a3-fa2a-4d35-9a92-273c606e587a_748x626.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F072101a3-fa2a-4d35-9a92-273c606e587a_748x626.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F072101a3-fa2a-4d35-9a92-273c606e587a_748x626.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://www.edisonresearch.com/twitter-x-usage-sees-sharp-decline/">全国广播公司</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>有趣的是，当我遇到 20 岁出头到 20 岁左右的人时，他们不想像 2010 年代的年轻人那样通过 Instagram、Twitter 或 Facebook Messenger 进行联系。他们只是交换电话号码，就像 2000 年代的人们那样。每个人仍然始终在线，但“在线”越来越意味着群聊、Discord 和其他小组互动。作为一个社会，我们正在重新学习如何将我们的社交生活围绕我们在现实生活中认识的人网络中心，而不是围绕我们向一群陌生人广播我们的行为和想法的表演性信息源。</p><p>好的。</p><p>但我怀疑还有一些其他趋势促使年轻人离开公共互联网并进入更多的私人空间。在过去的几年里，许多力量已经改变了社交媒体和传统网络。其中一些使公共互联网的体验变得更加无聊，而另一些则将其变成了更类似于电视的东西。以下是我看到的一些趋势：</p><h4>广告吞噬了免费互联网（“enshittification”）</h4><p> “enshittification”这个词是由科里·多克托罗（Cory Doctorow）创造的，他是我最喜欢的科幻作家之一，也是互联网趋势的敏锐观察者。在<a href="https://doctorow.medium.com/social-quitting-1ce85b67b456">2022 年的 Medium 帖子</a>和<a href="https://www.wired.com/story/tiktok-platforms-cory-doctorow/">2023 年的 Wired 文章</a>中，他认为社交媒体平台具有可预测的生命周期：</p><ol><li><p>首先，它以出色（且免费）的用户体验吸引了一批用户，创造了一种网络效应，让人们难以离开。</p></li><li><p>然后，为了赚钱，它通过出售用户数据、向用户发送垃圾广告等行为吸引了一批商业客户。这使得用户体验变差，但用户却被网络效应困在平台上。</p></li><li><p>最后，该平台试图通过提高费用、提供自己的竞争产品等方式从企业客户那里获取更多价值。这使得该平台对于企业客户来说是一个更糟糕的价值主张，但由于所有用户仍然在平台上，而由于自身的沉没成本，广告商也无法离开。这就是蒂姆·奥莱利所说的“ <a href="https://voicebot.ai/2017/09/27/tim-oreilly-says-dont-eat-ecosystem-lesson-voice-platforms/">吞噬生态系统</a>”。</p></li></ol><p>这是社交媒体平台运作方式的一个非常合理的模型。由于平台网络效应使用户远离传统网站，因此它越来越多地描述整个公共互联网的运作方式。</p><p>但对于大多数普通人来说，唯一重要的一步是第二步——广告的不断扩散以及以前用户友好的社交媒体平台通过眼球获利的其他方式。</p><p>谷歌就是一个很好的例子。多年来，谷歌一直是互联网的首页——一个简单明了的文本栏，您可以在其中输入您要查找的内容，并立即找到为您提供所需信息的网站。然而，近年来，谷歌通过增加平台上的广告量，不断地通过其广告搜索垄断货币化。例如，如果我想在网络上了解无人机，曾经有一段时间我只需搜索“无人机”即可。现在，结果的第一页和第二页都是试图让我购买无人机的广告： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3baa3b0-64ff-44e0-84a7-41fdf2747a71_1659x855.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3baa3b0-64ff-44e0-84a7-41fdf2747a71_1659x855.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc3baa3b0-64ff-44e0-84a7-41fdf2747a71_1659x855.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/http