o:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1cf8cd8-e6a3-468c-8006-bb32681a3daa_807x762.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1cf8cd8-e6a3-468c-8006-bb32681a3daa_807x762.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1cf8cd8-e6a3-468c-8006-bb32681a3daa_807x762.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1cf8cd8-e6a3-468c-8006-bb32681a3daa_807x762.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1cf8cd8-e6a3-468c-8006-bb32681a3daa_807x762.jpeg" width="596" height="562.7657992565056" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c1cf8cd8-e6a3-468c-8006-bb32681a3daa_807x762.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:762,&quot;width&quot;:807,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:596,&quot;bytes&quot;:168656,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1cf8cd8-e6a3-468c-8006-bb32681a3daa_807x762.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1cf8cd8-e6a3-468c-8006-bb32681a3daa_807x762.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1cf8cd8-e6a3-468c-8006-bb32681a3daa_807x762.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc1cf8cd8-e6a3-468c-8006-bb32681a3daa_807x762.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>从任何单一污水生成器的角度来看，生成越来越多的污水可能是一个经济上合理的主张。但它产生了负外部性，即其他人的互联网体验变得越来越无聊、有点令人讨厌的废话。未来，问题可能会变得更加严重；人工智能甚至可能会在人工智能生成的斜坡上<a href="https://www.popularmechanics.com/technology/a44675279/ai-content-model-collapse/">训练自己</a>，将整个互联网变成一个递归的斜坡乌洛波洛斯。 “<a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/danidiplacido/2024/01/16/the-dead-internet-theory-explained/">死亡互联网理论</a>”目前是一个愚蠢有趣的阴谋论，但它可能在不远的将来成为现实。</p><h4>谎言之神进入谎言之网</h4><p>已故的<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/go-read-some-vernor-vinge">弗诺·文奇（Vernor Vinge）</a>是我一直以来最喜欢的科幻小说作家之一，他写了一个系列，其中银河互联网被称为<a href="https://reactormag.com/the-net-of-a-million-lies-vernor-vinges-a-fire-upon-the-deep/">“百万谎言之网”</a> （显然是在取笑他自己在新闻组上的经历）。这与一句俗话“谎言可以走遍半个地球，真相才得以出现”有关——因为制造错误信息的边际成本远小于反驳错误信息的边际成本，这是一个自由、非中介的市场的想法往往会传播很多谎言。大量研究表明，错误信息<a href="https://news.mit.edu/2018/study-twitter-false-news-travels-faster-true-stories-0308">在社交媒体上的传播速度实际上比真实信息更快</a>。</p><p>这就是为什么人类传统上依赖信息看门人——报纸编辑、电视主播等——来防止我们成为全职事实核查者。社交媒体上很少有这样的看门人，2016 年大选后，关于我们是否需要某种企业编辑控制以减少社交媒体上传播的错误信息量，存在着一场巨大的（且持续的）辩论。</p><p>我不会在这里重述这场争论，但我会说生成式人工智能绝对会加剧这个问题。现在，制作某人声音的深度伪造品几乎是轻而易举的事，经过人工智能处理的图像也很容易，而且深度伪造视频也正在实现这一目标。这不是未来的推测问题——它现在正在发生。</p><p>人工智能造假可<a href="https://www.cnn.com/2024/02/04/asia/deepfake-cfo-scam-hong-kong-intl-hnk/index.html">用于诈骗</a>：</p><blockquote><p>据香港警方称，一家跨国公司的一名财务人员在一次视频电话会议中被骗，利用 Deepfake 技术冒充该公司首席财务官，向诈骗者支付了 2500 万美元。</p><p>香港警方在周五的新闻发布会上表示，在这个精心策划的骗局中，这名员工被骗去参加视频通话，他以为是其他几名工作人员，但实际上所有这些人都是深度伪造的娱乐产品。</p></blockquote><p> AI造假可用于<a href="https://www.thebaltimorebanner.com/education/k-12-schools/eric-eiswert-ai-audio-baltimore-county-YBJNJAS6OZEE5OQVF5LFOFYN6M/">个人报复</a>：</p><blockquote><p>巴尔的摩县警方逮捕<strong> </strong>周四上午，派克斯维尔高中前体育主任指控他涉嫌使用人工智能冒充校长埃里克·艾斯沃特 (Eric Eiswert)，导致公众相信艾斯沃特在闭门后发表<a href="https://www.thebaltimorebanner.com/education/k-12-schools/pikesville-high-principal-eric-eiswert-NT7K7N4K6RDEJNL5Z7ULTEG7VY/">种族主义和反犹太主义言论</a>……达里恩 (Darien) 被指控扰乱学校活动。调查人员确定他伪造了艾斯沃特的声音，并于一月份在社交媒体上传播了该音频[.]</p></blockquote><p>人工智能造假可<a href="https://www.cnn.com/2024/02/01/politics/election-deepfake-threats-invs/index.html">用于政治</a>：</p><blockquote><p>斯洛伐克即将举行决定谁将领导国家的关键选举，几天前，一段令人震惊的录音在网上传播，其中一位顶级候选人似乎吹嘘他如何操纵选举……该录音立即在社交媒体上疯传，这位亲北约并与西方利益一致的候选人于9月被支持与莫斯科和俄罗斯总统弗拉基米尔·普京建立更密切关系的对手击败。</p><p>虽然泄露的音频影响的选票数量仍不确定，但现在有两件事已经非常清楚：这些录音是假的，是使用人工智能创建的；美国官员将欧洲发生的这一事件视为美国在 2024 年总统选举期间可能会经历的那种干扰的可怕预兆。</p></blockquote><p>人工智能造假甚至可以<a href="https://petapixel.com/2024/04/15/netflix-accused-of-using-ai-photos-in-true-crime-documentary/">用于企业媒体内容</a>：</p><blockquote><p> Netflix 被指控​​在一部新的真实犯罪纪录片<em>《詹妮弗做了什么》</em>中使用了人工智能处理的图像……这部纪录片围绕着詹妮弗·潘展开，她被判雇佣杀人袭击她的父母。纪录片大约 28 分钟后，潘的高中好友 Nam Nguyen 被描述为一个“活泼、快乐、自信且非常真诚”的人。他的话还附有一系列相关照片……但仔细观察这些图像，有被篡改的迹象；特别是一张显示潘双臂闪烁和平手势的图像似乎被公然操纵，这提供了证据表明至少部分图像是人工智能生成的。</p></blockquote><p>目前尚不清楚如何控制深度造假。各国都在<a href="https://www.understandingai.org/p/states-are-racing-ahead-of-congress">急于推出旨在限制深度造假的法规</a>，但随着技术的进步，检测深度造假的技术是否仍然可行还不确定。未来一种可能的平衡是，人们学会不相信他们在公共互联网（或未经验证的电话、短信或电子邮件）上看到或听到的任何东西。</p><p> Perhaps we&#39;ve finally perfected the Net of Lies by creating a God of Lies to rule over it.</p><p> So the internet as we know it — social media sites and the Web — is becoming a generally worse place to hang out. Wading through oceans of advertisements, algorithmic randomness antisemitic Russian bots, Tiktok-poisoned shouters, AI slop, and deepfakes is just not a fun way to spend anyone&#39;s precious limited lifetime.</p><p> Better, perhaps, to simply withdraw from the public internet — to spend one&#39;s time chatting directly with friends and in small groups, having fun offline, and maybe watching TV or reading a book or a Substack. That sort of human interaction worked fine before the internet, and it will probably work just fine today. Which is why despite the fact that all of the trends I mentioned are negative, I&#39;m optimistic about the future of our digital communications and our media diet. Maybe someday historians will look back on the era when we lived our lives on social networking sites as a brief anomaly. </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-death-again-of-the-internet-as?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-death-again-of-the-internet-as?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p><p></p><p></p>; 
